    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Claims that in-person schooling has not amplified SARS-CoV-2 transmission are based on similar infection rates in schools and their surrounding communities and limited numbers of documented in-school transmission events. Simulations assuming high in-school transmission suggest that these metrics cannot exclude the possibility that transmission in schools exacerbated overall pandemic risks.</jats:p>",
